/*Implementation of a grid system*/
/*Inspiration found @ http://flexboxgrid.com*/


/* Documentation:
.container--grid is for static containers (not really what you want for responsive)
.container--fluid is for percentage widths that are fluid across screen sizes (favor this container over container--grid!)

REQUIRED USAGE:
.container--fluid
  .row--grid
    .col--*
    .col--*
    .col--* + ...

inside of a .container--fluid, add a div with .row--grid to set up the flex grid.
inside of a .row--grid, add .col--[SIZE]-[WIDTH] (eg .col--sm-6) classes.

BREAKPOINT SIZE MODIFIERS:
Size options include xs,sm,md, and lg.
.xs will handle all screen sizes, .sm handles 768px and up, .md for 1024px and up, and .lg for 1200px and up.

WIDTHS:
Column width modifiers range from 1 to 12 and adjust how many columns a cell will span
the WIDTH may be optionally left off of classes for flexbox to auto adjust widths (it splits each .col width evenly)

OFFSETS:
to offset a cell WIDTH columns, a .col--[SIZE]-offset-[WIDTH] (eg .col--sm-offset-5) may be added

ALIGNMENT MODIFIERS:
To modify the alignment of rows, add a modifier class on the same level as the .row--grid class
.[MODIFIER]--[SIZE] (eg .start--xs)

MODIFIERs include:
.start:     cells are aligned to the left if cells don't take up full row width
.center     cells are centered if cells don't take up full row width
.end        cells are aligned to the right if cells don't take up full row width
.top        cells are vertically top-aligned
.middle     cells are vertically aligned to the middle
.bottom     cells are vertically aligned to the bottom
.between    any extra space cells do not take up is put between the cells
.around     any extra space cells do not take up is put around the cells

ORDER:
may be added to cells to put override them as the first of last displayed child in the row:
.first--SIZE
.last--size

HIDING:
.hide--SIZE can be used to hide cells on specific breakpoints.

***NOTE*** all breakpoints are done in an and-up manner, meaning:
xs will affect all screen sizes unlerss overridden by sm, md or lg
sm will affect screen sizes 768px and above unless overridden by md or lg
md will affect screen sizes 1024px and above unless overridden by lg
lg will affect screen sizes 1200px and above


*/

:root {
  --gutter-width: 1rem;
  --outer-margin: 2rem;
  --gutter-compensation: calc((var(--gutter-width) * 0.5) * -1);
  --half-gutter-width: calc((var(--gutter-width) * 0.5));
  --xs-min: 30;
  --sm-min: 48;
  --md-min: 64;
  --lg-min: 75;
  --screen-xs-min: var(--xs-min)em;
  --screen-sm-min: var(--sm-min)em;
  --screen-md-min: var(--md-min)em;
  --screen-lg-min: var(--lg-min)em;
  --container-sm: calc(var(--sm-min) + var(--gutter-width));
  --container-md: calc(var(--md-min) + var(--gutter-width));
  --container-lg: calc(var(--lg-min) + var(--gutter-width));
}

